#%Module1.0
## opencode modulefile (Environment Modules, Tcl)
## Terminal coding agent, served by the local ai-session models.
##
## Source of truth: modulefiles/opencode/1.14.41 in the rcc-vllm repo.
## Install targets (symlink or copy from the repo -- never edit in place):
##   Tier 1 (testing):    /project/rcc/mehta5/modulefiles/opencode/1.14.41
##   Tier 3 (production): /software/modulefiles/opencode/1.14.41  (RCC-installed)
##
## The binary is the single-file release install at
## /project/rcc/mehta5/opencode/<version>/bin/opencode. This version (1.14.41)
## is the one the ai-session tool-tag workaround (AGENTS.md) was validated
## against; when upgrading, install the new version side by side under a new
## version directory + modulefile, re-run the opencode live checks, and only
## then retire this one.

proc ModulesHelp { } {
    puts stderr "opencode: a terminal coding agent."
    puts stderr "Use with the local models: module load ai-session; ai-session code --agent;"
    puts stderr "then run `opencode` in a project directory with an opencode.json"
    puts stderr "(`ai-session connect` prints one). Docs: https://rmehta1987.github.io/rcc-vllm/"
}

module-whatis "opencode terminal coding agent (pairs with ai-session local models)"

conflict opencode

prepend-path PATH /project/rcc/mehta5/opencode/1.14.41/bin
